review_blob: Huge roasted coffee and chocolate flavors! Slight bitter aftertaste. Perfect for a cold winter afternoon.

Puts an inky black with a creamy ran head that dissipates quickly. Coffee and dark chocolate nose. Roasty coffee taste, rich mouth feel with a creamy smooth finish. Some bitterness lingers on the tongue. Nice!
beer_name: Left Hand Bittersweet Imperial Coffee Milk Stout

review_blob: Poured from a 341 ml bottle. Opaque black with a tan head that dissipated quickly. Dark chocolate and roasted malt on the nose. Those flavors continue on the palate with a hint of vanilla sweetness. Finish lingers with toasty goodness. A winner!
Pours a cloudy plum/pomegranate color--gorgeous. Tart and slightly funky taste. Subtle plum flavor. Refreshing. A damn fine beer!
beer_name: Uinta Crooked Line Birthday Suit: 22nd Anniversary

review_blob: Pours deep black with a tan head. Roasted malt and piney aroma. Dark roasted malt flavors balanced by piney hops. Hoppy finish lingers on the palate. Balanced.
beer_name: Stone Sublimely Self Righteous Black IPA

review_blob: 22 oz bottle. Poured black with a tan head. Heavy malt and coffee on the nose and continues on the palate. The rye comes in on the finish. Paired very well with a piece of tiramisu. Very enjoyable!
beer_name: Lagunitas ScareCity #3: High West-ified Imperial Coffee Stout

review_blob: Pours a nice mahogany color. Nutty aroma. Big hazelnut flavor with a malty finish. One of my favorite beers.
Pours a dark brown with minimal lacing on the glass. Roasted malt aroma. Bitter chocolate and coffee flavors. Dry finish. Very enjoyable.

Pours a light golden color with a thin head and lacing in the glass. Initial nose is of grapefruit and pine. Thin mouthfeel. Grapefruit with a bitter piney finish. Epic brews some great beers. This one is just average.
Gorgeous deep amber color. Highly carbonated. Piney grapefruit bitterness. Solid IPA but not my favorite.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Double Wide I.P.A.

review_blob: Inky black pour with a dark brown head. Roasted malt aroma. Thick mouth feel. Coffee and some licorice flavors. Roasted flavor lingers on the palate with a boozy finish. Very good!
Pours an inviting honey color. Nose is grapefruit and pine. Grapefruit is first taste on the palate with a piney hop finish. Very balanced. Paired well with a burger and spicy fries. Very nice.
Fruity aroma. Golden yellow color. Malty upfront yielding to a pleasant hoppy finish. Paired well with mild Mexican food.
Pours a deep red brown. Floral and sweet nose. Beautiful balance between the malt and hops. Piney finish. A great beer.
Pours a beautiful copper red color. Nose is sweet with piney citrus. Medium bodied. Grapefruit with pine finish. Pairs very well with Mexican food. Very nice.
22oz bomber. Deep mahogany color. Mild carbonation. Well balanced with some pumpkin spice offset by a mild hop flavor. One of my favorite pumpkin beers.
beer_name: Epic / DC Brau Fermentation Without Representation

review_blob: From a bottle. Pours a hazy orange. Aromas of pine and grapefruit. Medium body. Pine and grapefruit flavors with a nice bitter aftertaste. Very balanced and drinkable. One of my favorites.
Pours a hazy orange color. Nose is of pine. Lots of pine and resin flavors. Finishes with a bitter lingering aftertaste.
I found this beer to be a middle of the road IPA. It had a funky aftertaste.
